Robson, Ray (2690) - So, Wesley (2774)
U.S. Championship (chess24.com) [7] 2022.10.12
E50 Nimzo-Indian, 4.e3 e8g8, 5.Nf3, without ...d5

1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 e6 3.Nc3 Bb4 4.e3 O-O 5.Nf3 Bxc3+ 6.bxc3 d6 7.Bd3 e5 8.e4 Re8 9.O-O exd4 10.cxd4 Nxe4 11.Re1 Nf6 12.Rxe8+ Qxe8 13.h3 Nbd7 14.Qc2 b6 15.Bb2 Bb7 16.d5 Qf8 17.g4 h6 18.Kh2 c6 19.g5 hxg5 20.Nxg5 cxd5 21.Bh7+ Kh8 22.Bf5 Ne5 23.f4 Ng6 24.Bxf6 gxf6 25.Nxf7+ Qxf7 26.Bxg6 Qe7 27.Qf2 f5 28.Rg1 Rg8 29.Rg5 Rg7 30.Qh4+ Kg8 31.Qh5 Bc8 32.cxd5 a5 33.Qh6 b5 34.Bh7+ Kf8 35.Rg2

The 2022 U.S. Championship is a 14-player round-robin featuring the strongest players in the USA, who compete for $262,000 in prize money as well as the coveted title of U.S. Champion. If two or more players tie for first place a playoff will be held.

Players receive 90 minutes for the first 40 moves followed by 30 minutes for the rest of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. Draw offers are not allowed before move 30. Official website: uschesschamps.com
